Durban &nbsp;A 12-year-old boy was killed when he was struck by a minibus taxi as he chased after a soccer ball in Durban on Friday, paramedics said.Rescue Care Paramedics spokeswoman Cerron Lennox said that the boy sustained multiple injuries and had succumbed to them before paramedics arrived on scene. He was declared dead at the scene. The accident happened on Booth Road in Cato Manor, shortly before 5pm. Police and eThekwini Metro Police were on scene investigating the accident. African News Agency